England making finals and semi-finals is rare, certainly in my lifetime. "Football's coming home" isn't a brag, it's a reflection on how shit we've been over 60 years, how many times we've fucked up.

It's been 2 semi-finals in 60 years.

But the difference is we're now making them, time and time again, this England team are now part of the elite. Euros back to back finals, WC Semis consistently.

We have a whole generation of fans who only know England getting to semi-finals and beyond. We're a different beast now.

We won't be going anywhere, expect us to be at the top in every major tournament from here on out. We've now proven that we're one of the best.

Argentina deserved it tonight, but holy shit what a World Cup from the lads, what a battle throughout every game. 

A young England squad, Bellingham at 23, a team packed with youth as others begin to end their golden generations, this is the future.

Well done England, unbelievable memories again, a World Cup experience I'll never forget and forever grateful I was there to experience it.

Another case of "what if" but I've loved every moment and couldn't be prouder of this fucking team.

